---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import RefiCalc from '../../components/RefiCalc.astro';
const productSchema={"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": ["FinancialProduct", "Service"], "name": "DSCR Loan Refinance", "description": "Refinance an investment property based on its rental income \u2014 no personal income documentation required.", "provider": {"@type": "Organization", "name": "Stairway Mortgage"}, "areaServed": "US"};
const faqSchema={"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question", "name": "Can I take cash out with a DSCR refinance?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. A cash-out DSCR refinance lets you access equity while qualifying on the property's rental income. Many investors use this to fund the next acquisition."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What DSCR ratio do I need to refinance?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Most programs look for a ratio of at least 1.0 (the property covers its own debt), with 1.25+ often unlocking the best pricing. Some lenders allow sub-1.0 with compensating factors."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Do I need to show my tax returns?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "No. DSCR refinances qualify on the property's cash flow, not your personal income \u2014 that's the core advantage for self-employed and portfolio investors."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Can I refinance a hard-money loan into a DSCR loan?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes \u2014 this is one of the most common uses. Investors often use a DSCR refinance to exit a short-term, high-rate hard-money loan into longer-term financing once a property is stabilized."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Can I refinance multiple rental properties?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Many investors refinance several properties; some use a portfolio loan to combine them. We can discuss the best structure for your holdings."}}]};
const breadcrumbSchema={"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://stairwaymortgage.com/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Loan Programs", "item": "https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "DSCR Loan Refinance"}]};
---

<Layout title="DSCR Loan Refinance | Stairway" description="Refinance an investment property based on its rental income — no personal income documentation required." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/dscr-loan-refinance/">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(productSchema)} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(breadcrumbSchema)} />
  <nav class="container-page lp-breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/loan-programs/">Loan Programs</a> <span>/</span> <span>DSCR Loan Refinance</span>
  </nav>
  <header class="container-prose lp-header">
    <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-blue mb-5">Loan Program · Refinance</span>
    <h1 class="display-lg">DSCR Loan Refinance: Refinance Rentals on Property Cash Flow</h1>
    <p class="lede lp-lede">Refinance an investment property based on its rental income — no personal income documentation required. Guided by Jim Blackburn · <span class="mono">NMLS #1072866</span></p>
    <div class="lp-cta-row"><a href="/same-day-approval/" class="btn btn-blue btn-arrow">See My Options</a><a href="tel:+19549931625" class="btn btn-ghost">(954) 993-1625</a></div>
  </header>
  <article class="container-prose prose-editorial lp-body" set:html={`<h2><b>What an DSCR Loan Refinance Is</b></h2><p>A DSCR loan refinance lets real estate investors refinance a rental property using the property's cash flow rather than personal income. Whether you're lowering a rate, pulling cash out to acquire the next property, or exiting a hard-money loan, qualification rests on the property's debt service coverage ratio — not your tax returns.</p><h2><b>Who It's For</b></h2><ul><li>Investors refinancing out of a high-rate or hard-money loan</li><li>Owners pulling cash out to scale their portfolio</li><li>Self-employed investors whose tax returns understate their income</li><li>Borrowers who want qualification based on the property, not personal income</li></ul><h2><b>How It Works</b></h2><p>The lender calculates the property's DSCR — its monthly rent divided by its monthly debt obligation (principal, interest, taxes, insurance, HOA). A ratio of 1.0 means the property covers itself; higher ratios unlock better terms. For a cash-out DSCR refinance, you access equity while still qualifying purely on the property's numbers, which is what makes it powerful for investors growing a portfolio.</p><h2><b>Frequently Asked Questions</b></h2><h3><b>Can I take cash out with a DSCR refinance?</b></h3><p>Yes. A cash-out DSCR refinance lets you access equity while qualifying on the property's rental income. Many investors use this to fund the next acquisition.</p><h3><b>What DSCR ratio do I need to refinance?</b></h3><p>Most programs look for a ratio of at least 1.0 (the property covers its own debt), with 1.25+ often unlocking the best pricing. Some lenders allow sub-1.0 with compensating factors.</p><h3><b>Do I need to show my tax returns?</b></h3><p>No. DSCR refinances qualify on the property's cash flow, not your personal income — that's the core advantage for self-employed and portfolio investors.</p><h3><b>Can I refinance a hard-money loan into a DSCR loan?</b></h3><p>Yes — this is one of the most common uses. Investors often use a DSCR refinance to exit a short-term, high-rate hard-money loan into longer-term financing once a property is stabilized.</p><h3><b>Can I refinance multiple rental properties?</b></h3><p>Yes. Many investors refinance several properties; some use a portfolio loan to combine them. We can discuss the best structure for your holdings.</p>`} />
  <div class="container-prose"><RefiCalc mode="cash-out" /></div>
  <div class="container-prose"><p class="lp-compliance mono">This page is for educational purposes and is not a commitment to lend or an offer of a specific rate. Loan terms, rates, and qualification depend on your individual circumstances and are subject to underwriting approval. Stairway Mortgage is a division of NEXA Mortgage LLC.</p></div>

  <section class="section-tight lp-final-cta"><div class="container-prose"><div class="card lp-final-cta__card">
    <h2 class="display-md">Is refinancing right for you?</h2>
    <p class="lede">We'll run your real numbers and tell you straight whether it pencils — no credit pull to start.</p>
    <a href="/schedule-call/" class="btn btn-blue btn-arrow">Talk to Our Team</a>
  </div></div></section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .lp-breadcrumb { font-family:var(--font-mono); font-size:12px; color:var(--color-mute); padding-top:2rem; padding-bottom:1.25rem; }
  .lp-breadcrumb a { color:var(--color-mute); text-decoration:none; } .lp-breadcrumb a:hover { color:var(--color-blue); }
  .lp-breadcrumb span { margin-inline:0.4rem; opacity:0.5; }
  .lp-header h1 { margin-bottom:1.25rem; } .lp-lede { margin-bottom:1.5rem; }
  .lp-cta-row { display:flex; gap:0.75rem; flex-wrap:wrap; }
  .lp-body { margin-top:2.5rem; }
  .lp-body :global(h2) { font-family:var(--font-display); font-variation-settings:"opsz" 96; font-weight:500; font-size:clamp(1.6rem,3vw,2.25rem); line-height:1.15; margin-top:3rem; margin-bottom:1.1rem; }
  .lp-body :global(h3) { font-family:var(--font-display); font-weight:500; font-size:clamp(1.2rem,2vw,1.55rem); margin-top:2rem; margin-bottom:0.8rem; }
  .lp-body :global(p) { font-size:17px; line-height:1.75; margin-bottom:1.25rem; color:var(--color-ink-light); }
  .lp-body :global(ul) { margin:0 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:0.5rem; }
  .lp-body :global(li) { font-size:17px; line-height:1.65; }
  .lp-body :global(a) { color:var(--color-blue); text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:2px; }
  .lp-compliance { font-size:11px; line-height:1.6; color:var(--color-mute); padding:1.5rem 0; border-top:1px solid var(--color-bone); margin-top:2rem; letter-spacing:0.01em; }
  .lp-final-cta__card { text-align:center; display:flex; flex-direction:column; align-items:center; gap:1rem; padding:2.5rem; }
</style>
